meta {
  name: GET charging power-curve (v2.10.0)
  type: http
  seq: 40
}

get {
  url: {{charging_host_url}}/charging_statistics/{{vin}}/power-curve
  body: none
  auth: bearer
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{access_token}}
}

headers {
  Accept: application/json
}

docs {
  v2.10.0 - Per-session power-curve samples on the CARIAD charging-
  stats host (same vhost as seq 39).

  Returns the most recent completed charging session's per-sample
  power curve, suitable for graphing kW over time / SoC. Drives the
  ``last_charging_power_curve_points`` sensor whose state is the
  COUNT of samples; the full sample list lives in the entity's
  attributes (HA recorder friendly).

  Endpoint reference: Timwun/Cupra-WeConnect-Bruno-Collection
  (Charging Statistics power-curve sequence), independently parsed
  in seat_cupra._get_from_charging_host + ``get_status`` v2.10.0.

  Response shape:
    {
      "powerCurve": [
        {
          "timestamp": "2026-05-30T18:42:11Z",
          "soc_pct": 42,
          "power_kw": 124.5
        },
        ...
      ]
    }

  Newer firmware ships the list under data.powerCurve or under
  "samples" / "points"; the parser tries all variants defensively.

  Soft-fails to {} on 401 / 403 / 404 with the same semantics as
  /charging_statistics (seq 39).
}
